      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STORM SISTER (4) doesn't win out of turn but looks close to breaking through. Finished in the minors last time when second (17.05) at this track making it back to back placings. Has a good record here including three wins. Top prospect. REMEMBER JAY JAY (6) was prominent throughout when winning two back but could manage only midfield last time when 4th and beaten 7 lengths at Gawler (23.62). Can measure up this time. ON THE STRIP (2) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing fourth (20.27) in a TG1-4W at Angle Park. The form out of her last race has been franked. Worth following up. PHYLLOXERA FURY (1) placed last start at big odds and is in the mix again.",
